author: CNN
description:
At times shouting from the White House briefing room lectern, Vice President JD Vance fiercely defended the ICE agent who fatally shot a woman, calling the incident "an attack on law and order" and asserting that her death was "a tragedy of her own making." Former acting ICE director John Sandweg told CNN that it is "very disappointing" to see Vance "rush out to these conclusions" before an investigation is complete. The Minnesota Bureau of Criminal Apprehension said that the FBI is blocking them from the shooting investigation.

author: CNN
description:
We’re on the ground at CES in Las Vegas all week to sift through the hype and find the products that should actually be worth your money this year. Check out our guide to CES 2026 for our latest hands-on impressions right from the show floor.

We see tons of wacky laptops with rotating, expanding or foldable screens among the latest tech products at CES, but it’s very rare that those concepts become actual releases you might want to buy. That’s why I’m happy to see that, for the second year in a row, Lenovo has brought one of its head-turning prototypes to market with the ThinkBook Plus Gen 7 Auto Twist, a notebook with a swiveling display that can follow you around and open and close without you lifting a finger.
